# Phase 2 Fullstack Todo App - Environment Configuration
#
# This is a monorepo with separate backend and frontend applications.
# Each application has its own environment variables.
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#
# 1. Backend Environment (.env in src/core/backend/)
#    - Copy src/core/backend/.env.example to src/core/backend/.env
#    - Fill in your backend database URL and JWT secret
#
# 2. Frontend Environment (.env.local in src/core/frontend/)
#    - Copy src/core/frontend/.env.example to src/core/frontend/.env.local
#    - Fill in your Better Auth database URL and secrets
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
# - The JWT_SECRET must be the SAME in both backend and frontend
# - Backend and frontend use DIFFERENT databases (backend: tasks, frontend: users)
# - Never commit actual .env files to version control
# - Use strong random secrets in production
#
# Generate random secrets with: openssl rand -base64 32
